					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Uchuu Kebatail SDF definitly uses many of MMC5 graphics features.
<br />Just Breed is worth a look, it uses the MMC5 to have much more tiles on screen at the same time. Non-NES devloppers will just say that the game has good graphics, but I myself think that backrgound are really enhenced, allowing more diferent kind of buildings, trees, and many details as most SNES game. It also features all monsters and allies drawn via BG on field, that couldn't be done trough a normal mapper (Fire Emblem does it, but with much less sort of people, and they all watches down when not moving unlike to Just Breed). However, each ally sprite is here twice in the CHROM, once for when it's BG and once for when it's sprite, I would found myself more interesting to use the same tiles for both, allowing an even higher quantity of graphics for the background or effects in battle.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
